                            <comment id="15390076" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Fri, 22 Jul 2016 19:26:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can the recovery be done server side ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
221	    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt;{
222	      admin.disableTable(sysTable);
223	      admin.snapshot(snapshot, sysTable);
224	      admin.enableTable(sysTable);
225	      backupId = admin.backupTables(userRequest);
226	      &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; backupId;
227	    } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (IOException e){
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the catch block, we don&apos;t know which step in the try block fails.&lt;br/&gt;
You can use a flag to record last successful step.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But I think recovery on server side makes more sense.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
